PrecisAmendment to the FOOD AND DRUG REGULATIONS (Schedule No. 918) providing for the use of alpha-amylase (an enzyme derived from two strains of Bacillus licheniformis) in the hydrolysis of edible starches for the production of dextrins, maltose, dextrose, glucose and glucose solids, and used extensively in the production of brewer's mash and distillers' mash.
RegistrationRegistration: SOR/ 1994-0552 Publication Date: 1994-09-07
Attachments
precis:
Amendment to the FOOD AND DRUG REGULATIONS (Schedule No. 918) providing for
the use of alpha-amylase (an enzyme derived from two strains of Bacillus
licheniformis) in the hydrolysis of edible starches for the production of
dextrins, maltose, dextrose, glucose and glucose solids, and used
extensively in the production of brewer's mash and distillers' mash.
